{
  "texts": [
    "Subsequently, Ultron [371] encoded documents into a latent semantic space using BERT [121], and compressed vectors into a smaller semantic space via Product Quantization (PQ) [73,102], preserving semantic information.",
    "Each document's PQ code serves as its semantic identifier.",
    "MEVI [346] clusters documents using Residual Quantization (RQ) [189] and utilizes dual-tower and seq2seq model embeddings for a balanced performance in large-scale document retrieval.Learnable DocIDs.",
    "Unlike previous static DocIDs, GenRet [265] proposed learnable document representations, transforming documents into DocIDs through an encoder, then reconstructs documents from DocIDs using a decoder, trained to minimize reconstruction error.",
    "Furthermore, it used progressive training and diversity clustering for optimization."
  ]
}